description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Come and join a Trust rated Outstanding by the CQC. South Warwickshire NHS Foundation have been rated as outstanding following our latest inspection by the CQC and we are recruiting new staff to come and help us improve even further.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Band 5 - £24,907 - £ 30,615 plus overtime opportunities, 27 days holiday and Bank holidays and voluntary pension scheme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Estates Department provides a comprehensive maintenance repair and installation service of buildings, grounds, engineering services and associated equipment throughout the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to work on our on-call roster over a 4 week period.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This may vary from time to time depending on staffing levels and work commitments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB SUMMARY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To work autonomously as an electrical crafts person who will be part of an in house reactive maintenance department who will be responsible for prioritising daily workloads and fault diagnosis of plant and equipment as well as preventative planned maintenance schedules across all trust properties.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post requires that the individual is a team player who can also work on His / Her own and make sound judgement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Minimum requirement City and Guilds Certificated (or similar) with 3 years’ experience in an electrical maintenance or electrical installation environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;18th Edition mandatory, Testing and Inspection preferable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is Monday- Friday with opportunities for overtimes and weekend working. Start and finishing times 8.00 am to 4.00 pm.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;May be required to take part in an emergency on-call rota.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mark Wise for an informal chat 01926 495321 ex 8542&lt;/p&gt;
